I've given up on it. The design is fantastic, the Google Play Games integration is cool; it shows GREAT promise. Unfortunately, the most useful feature to me - its integration with Android Wear - is broken. If you enter a drink when you're away from your phone, it never syncs, and half the time, even if your phone is CONNECTED, it doesn't sync properly. Additionally, the "hydration ratio" feature is a great idea, but its execution is at best half-baked, as they don't offer any guidelines for determining what the hydration ratio IS, nor do they offer ANY sample data for common beverages. Additionally, the integration with S-Health is rather poorly done. S-Health already has a tracker for water, but instead of sending data to it, this app creates its OWN, completely REDUNDANT tile.   In short, if you're willing to pull your phone out and log it directly on your device, and all you want is something that tracks the actual water you drink, this is a fine app (although the free version will server you just fine for that). If you're enticed by all of its extended features, don't bother. They're fantastic ideas with poor implementation.
